<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="548" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[811,1457,1300,1645]" box="[813,957,1300,1326]" pageId="23" pageNumber="548">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[811,1457,1300,1645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="548">
Test large in size, entirely planispiral and involute, subspherical to ovoid in shape, or subrhomboidal in some specimens with spherical initial volutions. The coiling of the spiral is moderately tight and followed by some loosely coiled last volution in some adult forms. Wall is thick and four-layered including tectum, diaphanotheca, lower and upper tectorium. 
<collectingRegion box="[811,869,1523,1549]" country="Spain" name="Ceuta" pageId="23" pageNumber="548">Septa</collectingRegion>
regularly and slightly folded across the centre of the test and folded near the polar extremities. Chomata are massive, symmetrical and rounded to subquadrate or short ribbon-like in some specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="548" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[811,1456,1683,1836]" box="[813,913,1683,1709]" pageId="23" pageNumber="548">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[811,1456,1683,1836]" pageId="23" pageNumber="548">
<taxonomicName authority="Akbas" authorityName="Akbas" authorityYear="2022" box="[813,1033,1714,1740]" class="Fusulinata" family="Fusulinellidae" genus="Praefusulinella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="23" pageNumber="548" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[813,962,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="548">Praefusulinella</emphasis>
Akbaş
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1042,1113,1715,1741]" pageId="23" pageNumber="548" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1342,1453,1714,1740]" class="Fusulinata" family="Fusulinellidae" genus="Fusulinella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="23" pageNumber="548" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1342,1453,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="548">Fusulinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
concerning the wall structure and septal fluting. However, the new genus differs by its thick wall, inflated subspherical to ovoid test shape and spherical initial volutions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
